=== Low speed limit ===

The mathematical by-product of this calculation is the mass–energy equivalence formula, that mass and energy are essentially the same thing:

formula_58

At a low speed (&quot;v&quot; ≪ &quot;c&quot;), the relativistic kinetic energy is approximated well by the classical kinetic energy. To see this, apply the binomial approximation or take the first two terms of the Taylor expansion in powers of formula_59 for the reciprocal square root:

formula_60

So, the total energy formula_61 can be partitioned into the rest mass energy plus the non-relativistic kinetic energy at low speeds.

When objects move at a speed much slower than light (e.g. in everyday phenomena on Earth), the first two terms of the series predominate. The next term in the Taylor series approximation

